171–Female":"1171–Deceased","1216":"1216","1227":"1227","about 1195":"about 1195","about 1215":"about 1215","1198":"1198","1196":"1196","1260":"1260","1171":"1171","1170":"1170","Stopham, West Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Stopham, West Sussex, England, United Kingdom","Stopham, Sussex, England":"Stopham, Sussex, England, United Kingdom","Stopham, Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Stopham, Sussex, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Barttelot","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Bartlett  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Bartlett","meanings":["English: from the Middle English and Old French personal name <i>Bertelot</i>, <i>Bartelot</i> (with the Old French double diminutive suffix <i>-elot</i>), a pet form of   Bartholomew  .","History: This is the name of a well-established New England family. Its members include Josiah Bartlett (1729–95), who was born in Amesbury, MA, and became governor of NH (1790–94). A Richard Bartlet(t) settled in Newbury, MA, in 1635."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Barttelot was born in 1196, in Stopham, Sussex, England, United Kingdom, his father, Adam Barttelot, was 26 and his mother, Mrs. Adam Barttelot, was 25. He married Mrs Robert Barttelot about 1215. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1227, in his hometown, at the age of 31."},"et":{"1196–1227":"1196–1227","–Female":"Surnud","1216–1260":"1216–1260","1170–1198":"1170–1198","1171–Female":"1171–Surnud","1216":"1216","1227":"1227","about 1195":"umbes 1195","about 1215":"umbes 1215","1198":"1198","1196":"1196","1260":"1260","1171":"1171","1170":"1170","Stopham, West Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Stopham, West Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stopham, Sussex, England":"Stopham, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stopham, Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Stopham, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1196–1227":"1196–1227","–Female":"Kuollut","1216–1260":"1216–1260","1170–1198":"1170–1198","1171–Female":"1171–Kuollut","1216":"1216","1227":"1227","about 1195":"noin 1195","about 1215":"noin 1215","1198":"1198","1196":"1196","1260":"1260","1171":"1171","1170":"1170","Stopham, West Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Stopham, West Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stopham, Sussex, England":"Stopham, Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stopham, Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Stopham, Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1196–1227":"1196–1227","–Female":"Décédée","1216–1260":"1216–1260","1170–1198":"1170–1198","1171–Female":"1171–Décédée","1216":"1216","1227":"1227","about 1195":"environ 1195","about 1215":"environ 1215","1198":"1198","1196":"1196","1260":"1260","1171":"1171","1170":"1170","Stopham, West Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Stopham, West Sussex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Stopham, Sussex, England":"Stopham, Sussex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Stopham, Sussex, England, Unite